description:
-- beautiful 2BR apartment; 
-- each room has its own bathroom;
-- furnished and ready for move-in;

-- great location - center of everything!

-- utilities are not included (but everything is connected and ready for use, including internet); month-to-month.

Live high above the trees in this top (8th) floor, 2 bedroom/2 bath apartment. Spectacular city views, yet peacefully above all the hustle and bustle. And just a short walk to the Metro or all the offerings of Dupont Circle, Logan Circle, 14th Street, U Street, and Adams Morgan. Located on 17th Street between R and S Streets, you'll be just steps from restaurants, shopping, nightlife, and park space. Grocery shopping is a block away, and Whole Foods and Trader Joe's are nearby.

Offering the charm and grace of an old-world, historic building, yet with modern conveniences: 
- Bright and sunny, with western and northern exposures - LOTS of windows; 
- Hardwood floors throughout; 
- New, high-efficiency central heating and A/C; 
- Washer/dryer in apartment; 
- Dishwasher; 
- Ceiling fans and track lighting; 
- Formal entry foyer; 
- Private balcony for enjoying those sunsets; 
- FIVE closets, PLUS a separate storage room; 
- 1,000 SF in a very livable floor plan; 
- Boutique condo building, professionally managed.

Enjoy the building's ROOFDECK with spectacular, panoramic views of the city, including the Washington Monument. Just in time for viewing the annual fireworks!

$3,500 per month, plus electric and internet/cable. 1-month's security deposit. 1-year lease. $50 application fee (per occupant).

Please, no pets and no smoking allowed.

Tenant pays for electric, internet, cable TV.
Typical underwriting standards require:
Minimum 680 credit score
Maximum rent to income ratio of 33%
Maximum total debt to income ratio of 50%
Income and employment verification
Landlord references
Credit check, with no history of past-due payments
Background check
